hivis.data

    public interface Data
    Interface for any object representing data. For example a series, table or graph. It provides some basic data storage (name, container DataSet) as well as a framework for handling changes to DataSets (see beginChanges(Object), setDataChanged(Object) and finishChanges(Object).
    Author:
    O. J. Coleman

    • Method Detail

      • isMutable

        boolean isMutable()
        Returns true iff the data represented by this Data set is mutable (either directly via setter methods or indirectly via other processes). The result of this method should not change over time.

      • equalTo

        boolean equalTo(Data data)
        Return true iff this Data set represents the same data as the given Data set.

      • equalToHashCode

        int equalToHashCode()
        Return a hash code consistent with equalTo(Data).

      • getContainers

        Set<Data> getContainers()
        Get the DataSets that "contain" this DataSet as part of their own data. For example a DataTable contains DataSeries.

      • addContainer

        void addContainer(Data container)
        Adds the given DataSet as a container for this DataSet, or if it has already been added makes no changes. Containers are notified of changes that occur to this DataSet via the setDataChanged(Object) method.

      • removeContainer

        void removeContainer(Data container)
        Removes the given DataSet as a container for this DataSet.

      • addChangeListener

        void addChangeListener(DataListener listener)
        Registers an object for notification of changes to the DataSet.
        Parameters:
        listener - the object to register.

      • removeChangeListener

        void removeChangeListener(DataListener listener)
        De-registers an object for notification of changes to the DataSet.
        Parameters:
        listener - the object to de-register.

      • beginChanges

        void beginChanges(Object changer)
        Notify this DataSet that changes are about to be made to it. lock() should generally be called at the beginning of this method.
        Parameters:
        changer - The object making the changes.

      • setDataChanged

        void setDataChanged(Object changeType)
        All implementations should call this method whenever the data is modified in some way. If any containers are set then the change will be registered with them too (see addContainer(Data)). If no object has registered that it is making multiple changes via beginChanges(Object) then a DataChangeEvent will be fired (see addChangeListener(DataListener)).

      • hasDataChanged

        boolean hasDataChanged()
        Returns true iff the data has been changed but a change event has not yet been fired.

      • changeInProgress

        boolean changeInProgress()
        Returns true iff any changers have indicated that they will modify the data.
        See Also:
        beginChanges(Object)

      • finishChanges

        void finishChanges(Object changer)
        Notify this DataSet that a set of changes to the data have been completed. If the data was changed and no other objects are modifying the data then a DataChangeEvent will be fired. unlock() should generally be called at the end of this method.

      • getCurrentChangers

        List<Object> getCurrentChangers()
        Get the list of objects that are currently changing the data, if any. A list is used for getCurrentChangers() so that duplicates may occur. This in order to handle cases such as a process changing a DataTable calling beginChanges() on the DataTable, and then beginChanges() on the individual DataSeries of the DataTable (resulting in more calls to beginChanges on the container DataTable) before calling finishChanges on the DataSeries and then the DataTable. In each call to finishChanges only one of the occurrences of the DataTable will be removed.
        See Also:
        beginChanges(Object)
